data.enText: the state or quality of being better, more skilful, more powerful, greater, etc. than others
the superiority of this operating system
data.chText: 这种操作系统的优越性

data.enText: to have naval/air superiority (= more ships/planes than the enemy)
behaviour that shows that you think you are better than other people
data.chText: 优越感；神气活现的样子；盛气凌人的行为

tr: displaying a sense of being better than others
example: he hated the white man's superiority and condescension

tr: the quality of being at a competitive advantage
the state of excelling or surpassing or going beyond usual limits

example.ex: The US will need a three-to-one superiority in forces to be sure of a successful attack...
example.tran: 美国需要在军力上具有3比1的优势才能确保进攻胜利。

value.def: If one side in a war or conflict has superiority, it has an advantage over its enemy, for example because it has more soldiers or better equipment.
value.tran: (战争或冲突中具有的)优势;优越(性)

trans: 自大情结，优越感(常为掩饰失败感)
